node.text:
Two of my Bugatti work in progress that has been stalled for a while (along with the Shelby cobra 2022) as I’ve been very busy getting contacts and commission work done. I should be getting back to these next week while focusing on finishing work this week and the coming weekend. 

One of them is the Bugatti Rafale in its very early stage, and will probably let undergo quite some change throughout the process. 
The other one is a much older one that I’ve been working on. No name yet lol. 

See ya ✌🏼

.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Alright, hear me out guys -
Break the rules. Design things out of the ordinary. Create your own rules, and directions. Bend them. Break them. Go nuts.

In this case, a design that is not based on anything at all other than a random sketch in my sketchbook. Inspired by so many other things, not just cars, but might see a lot of different inspiration from other cars and brands here. What I had in mind is simply designing a BMW and not following any BMW design DNA/language at all. And I like it - both the result, and the freedom. 

A BMW that you (obviously) didn’t expect to see. Some modern, retro. Futuristic touches overall and voila: 

BMW _ zero one 
@shift_alt_ego

•

node.text:
Only fair to whip out some more renders of the Mazda RXX that I’ve done a while ago. It’s been a while since I haven’t really focused on proper concepts of my own (not counting contract works) and was just working on aftermarket design to share on here.

I was always more drawn to car design, even more so than cars themselves and bodykits and all, as weird as that might sound. Working on aftermarket is really fun, it’s really something to be able to take the most precious cars and digitally waste them and not to forget - in the process making some people really really angry.. but it’s all fun! 

But… getting back to designing some other cars from scratch makes me feel more complete and I miss it whenever I’m not doing it. The whole process is so different, so much mor engaging. Makes you care more about what you’re doing rather than just… quick fenders and what not.

The RXX was done a while ago, and before that the Varano DeTomaso. And more are in the works! I’ve been working on a lot of them on an off these days and I’m trying my best to get the most possible done alongside long daily hours of work on other contracts and commissions.

Next is the BMW ZERO ONE, then hopefully the Shelby Cobra 2022! 

===========
Print giveaways 
The DeTomaso Varano and RXX prints gotta make their way to both winners - bear with me as our shop is still getting ready and I’m waiting for shipping to resume (after way way way too long!)

See ya! ✌🏼
